# Developer scratch and capture trees - do not ship
Latjo/
trace/

# Live capture reports (SCP03 live runs, eIM dumps, ...). These can
# contain derived session keys, chaining values, and IMSI/IMSI-mapped
# traces. Keep them out of git so they cannot be pushed by accident.
# `reports/.gitkeep` survives so the layout is documented.
reports/*
!reports/.gitkeep

# Packaging metadata written by `pip install -e .`
yggdrasim.egg-info/

# --- Universal GUI work-in-progress --------------------------------------
# The GUI implementation surface stays out of the public release tree so
# the published footprint stays stable. Drop these rules when the GUI
# graduates to a public release.
gui_frontend/
yggdrasim_common/gui_server/
tests/test_gui_*.py

# --- Internal planning / audit / handoff docs ----------------------------
# Per .cursor/rules/no-internal-roadmap-leaks.mdc: roadmap, release-audit,
# feature-plan, review and dated handoff / live-run reports are local-only
# and never tracked. Keep authoring drafts on disk if you like; do not
# commit them.
V1_*.md
V2_*.md
*_REVIEW.md
*_AUDIT.md
*_HANDOFF.md
*_handoff_*.md
*_RELEASE_NOTES.md
*_PATCHES.md
NEW_FEATURE_IDEAS.md
UPSTREAM_DEPENDENCY_NOTES.md

# --- Upstream-PR working tree -------------------------------------------
# Drop-in patch files we have authored against third-party dependencies
# (asn1tools, pySim, ...) and intend to submit upstream. The tree is
# strictly local: nothing here ships with the YggdraSIM wheel. Each file
# is self-contained Python plus an adjacent .md PR-description so it can
# be lifted into the corresponding upstream repo without modification.
upstream_patches/
site-docs/sources/V1_*.md
site-docs/sources/V2_*.md
site-docs/sources/*_REVIEW.md
site-docs/sources/*_AUDIT.md
site-docs/sources/*_HANDOFF.md
site-docs/sources/NEW_FEATURE_IDEAS.md
site-docs/sources/reports/